# Sync documentation on every change

After **any** implementation, refactor, bug fix, or config change in this project, update documentation **in the same session/PR** — not as a follow-up.

## Required files

| File | Keep accurate |
|------|----------------|
| `.sdd/specs/mac-world-clock/plan.md` | Current status, completed tasks, architecture notes, project layout, behaviors |
| `README.md` | Setup, build/run, features, usage, project structure, troubleshooting |

## Rules

1. **Same session** — doc updates ship with the code change, not later.
2. **Surgical edits only** — change sections affected by the work; do not rewrite unrelated content.
3. **No extra markdown** — do not create other `.md` files unless essential.
4. **Verify against code** — read changed source files before editing docs; do not guess.

## plan.md checklist

- **Current status** section reflects what is built vs pending.
- Mark implementation-order items done when implemented.
- Project layout lists actual paths (`Resources/Info.plist`, `AppDelegate.swift`, etc.).
- UI labels match code (e.g. **Done**, not **Save**).

## README.md checklist

- Features and usage match current UI and behavior.
- Build commands and `scripts/build-app.sh` subcommands stay accurate.
- Project layout mirrors the repo.
- Troubleshooting covers known constraints (e.g. launch-at-login requires `.app` bundle).

## Example

Changed `ConfigureTimezonesView` footer buttons → update plan.md configure-flow section **and** README usage if user-facing text changed.
